snippet: Talks planned for this week between the neighbors have been called off after a dispute over which delegates the countries would send.
abstract: Plans for first high-level government talks between North and South Korea in six years appear to have collapsed due to disagreement over which delegates countries would send and whether they were of similar rank.
lead_paragraph: Talks planned for this week between the neighbors have been called off after a dispute over which delegates the countries would send.

headline.main: North Korea’s Dialogue With the South Collapses
